This little hidden jewel was discovered yesterday while I was pumping gas across the street. There was a huge line starting from outside the door so I got curious. The place is called Dirty dogs, pretty much a hot dog joint with a mix to it. The hot dogs were pretty good and the price was decent. People were talking about the flaming elote which is covered in hot Cheeto powder, looked tasty but it wasn't. The Cheeto powder and the sweet corn didn't match at all, and on top of that the cilantro made it even worst. Rather than that I gave this place a 3 star.

Suede/velvet seating, low lighting and cozy space make this champagne bar a refined yet relaxed hangout for neighbors and those in the know. It's intimate and well serviced, two qualities the establishment preserves by under-advertising itself. Some of their house rules include "If you have found the place, don't tell anyone" and "Doors close to [further] visitors after 11pm" as well as "We only serve nice people".

Was beyond surprised when I stumbled in here dinner on a Friday. Bartenders are so friendly and the drinks are top notch. The music is what sealed the deal -- this guys aren't messing around and one drink led to four because of their hospitality and delivered ambience. Will come again.

I am confused and thoroughly disappointed.  We have gone to this Dive Bar for many years. We ordered our dinner tonight for delivery. I had been craving Dive bar's famous fries and Kentucky Bourbon wings. What arrived was not like anything we'd had there before. The fries were thin and dry, the wings were BONELESS, not much flavor,  just hot- nothing like what I had previously enjoyed at the Dive Bar-- and my husband's burger was like a hockey puck. We looked up photos online of the food we'd ordered afterwards because we wondered if the food had changed-- new menu or something. Everything looked as we remembered from before. So we are mystified and disappointed-- and we LOVE this place. Or rather loved it.
